SYNTECXHUB PROJECT 4
Project Title
Web Assessment Toolkit Development Using Python
Project Overview
During my internship at SyntexHub, I developed a Python-based Web Assessment Toolkit using Kali Linux and the Damn Vulnerable Web Application (DVWA) in a controlled lab environment. The aim of the project was to understand how web applications work and to build tools that can automate web application assessment tasks.
Project Development Steps
Set up the development environment using Python and a virtual environment.
Built a Form Mapper to discover web forms and input fields.
Developed a Web Crawler to automatically discover pages and create a sitemap.
Implemented Multi-Threaded Crawling to improve performance.
Generated CSV and HTML reports to document findings.
